
[1]implicitly

   IMPLIC'ITLY, adv. By inference deducible, but not expressed in words;
   virtually; in reality, but not in name.

   He that denies the providence of God, implicitly denies his existence.

   1. By connection with something else; dependently; with unreserved
   confidence; without doubting, or without examining evidence. We are
   disposed to believe implicitly what a man of veracity testifies.

   Learn not to dispute the methods of his providence,but humbly and
   implicitly to acquiesce in and adore them.
